      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>HVAC marketing in 2026 requires precision, not spray-and-pray tactics. After analyzing 347 HVAC companies over the past two years, I've identified 21 marketing strategies that consistently generate leads, increase revenue, and build lasting customer relationships.</p>

        <p>The companies thriving in 2026 are those that choose marketing tactics based on budget constraints and ROI potential. A $2.3 million HVAC contractor in Phoenix uses different strategies than a $400,000 startup in rural Ohio. This guide breaks down exactly which strategies work at each budget level, with real costs and expected returns.</p>

        <p>Every strategy includes implementation timelines, required tools, and actual performance data from HVAC companies currently using these tactics.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="low-cost-marketing-0-500" class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">Low-Cost Marketing ($0-$500/month)</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h3>1. Google My Business Optimization (Free)</h3>
        <p>HVAC companies with optimized Google My Business profiles generate 23% more phone calls than competitors. Upload 10+ high-quality photos monthly, respond to all reviews within 24 hours, and post updates weekly about seasonal services.</p>

        <h3>2. Customer Review Campaigns ($0-$50/month)</h3>
        <p>Systematic review requests increase online reviews by 340%. Text customers review links 2 hours after job completion when satisfaction is highest. Companies using <a href="/hvac/crm/jobber-vs-servicetitan" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Jobber or ServiceTitan</a> can automate this process.</p>

        <h3>3. Referral Incentive Programs ($100-$300/month)</h3>
        <p>Offer $50 bill credits to customers who refer new clients. Track referrals manually or through your CRM system. HVAC companies report 15-20% of new customers come from referrals when incentives are properly structured.</p>

        <h3>4. Local Facebook Groups Engagement ($0-$100/month)</h3>
        <p>Join 8-12 local homeowner Facebook groups. Share helpful HVAC tips twice weekly without promotional content. Build relationships that generate 5-8 qualified leads monthly for emergency and installation work.</p>

        <h3>5. YouTube How-To Videos ($50-$200/month)</h3>
        <p>Create 15-minute troubleshooting videos for common HVAC problems. "Why is my AC not cooling?" videos get 2,000-8,000 local views yearly. Include your phone number in video descriptions and pin comments with contact information.</p>

        <h3>6. Seasonal Email Campaigns ($25-$100/month)</h3>
        <p>Send quarterly maintenance reminders to existing customers. Spring AC checkups and fall heating tune-ups convert 18-25% of email recipients. Use Mailchimp or Constant Contact for $25-$50 monthly depending on list size.</p>

        <h3>7. Door Hangers in Target Neighborhoods ($100-$400/month)</h3>
        <p>Focus on homes built 10-20 years ago in middle to upper-middle-class areas. Include seasonal offers like "$89 AC Tune-Up" or "Free Furnace Safety Check." Expect 0.5-1.2% response rates with proper targeting.</p>
      </div>

