      <h2 id="mid-tier-marketing-500-1500" class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mt-8 mb-4">Mid-Tier Marketing ($500-$1,500/month)</h2>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h3>8. Google Ads for Emergency Services ($400-$800/month)</h3>
        <p>Target "emergency HVAC," "AC not working," and "furnace repair" keywords. Set budgets for $15-25 per click depending on market competition. Emergency service ads typically convert 8-12% of clicks into service calls.</p>

        <h3>9. Facebook and Instagram Advertising ($300-$600/month)</h3>
        <p>Run targeted campaigns to homeowners aged 35-65 within 15 miles of your service area. Promote seasonal services, financing options, and equipment replacements. Expect $25-50 cost per lead for qualified prospects.</p>

        <h3>10. Search Engine Optimization (SEO) ($500-$1,200/month)</h3>
        <p>Optimize your website for local keywords like "HVAC contractor [city name]" and "AC repair near me." Professional SEO services range $500-$1,200 monthly. Results typically appear after 3-6 months with 20-40% increase in organic traffic.</p>

        <h3>11. Direct Mail Campaigns ($600-$1,000/month)</h3>
        <p>Mail postcards or brochures to 2,000-5,000 homes monthly. Target neighborhoods with homes valued $200,000+ built 15-25 years ago. Include seasonal promotions and financing offers. Expect 1.5-2.8% response rates.</p>

        <h3>12. Vehicle Wraps and Fleet Branding ($200-$400/month amortized)</h3>
        <p>Professional vehicle wraps cost $2,500-$4,000 per truck but generate 600-1,200 daily impressions. Amortize costs over 12-24 months. Companies report 12-18% increase in brand recognition after fleet wrapping.</p>

        <h3>13. Radio Advertising ($400-$900/month)</h3>
        <p>Sponsor weather segments or home improvement shows on local radio stations. Focus on drive-time slots when homeowners commute. Radio advertising works best for brand awareness and generates 8-15 monthly inquiries.</p>

        <h3>14. Content Marketing Blog ($300-$700/month)</h3>
        <p>Publish 4-8 blog posts monthly about HVAC maintenance, energy efficiency, and seasonal tips. Hire freelance writers for $75-$150 per 1,000-word article. Blogs increase website traffic 25-45% within six months.</p>
      </div>

